<!DOCTYPE html>

<html lang="es">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>HUMANFITS — Week 1</title>
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Bebas+Neue&family=Barlow:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=Barlow+Condensed:ital,wght@0,400;0,600;0,700;1,400&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
<style>
  :root {
    --bg-primary: #070707;
    --bg-card: #0f0f0f;
    --bg-section: #0c0c0c;
    --yellow: #FFD600;
    --yellow-dim: #FFD60025;
    --yellow-glow: #FFD60055;
    --yellow-soft: #FFD60010;
    --white: #e8e8e8;
    --gray: #777777;
    --gray-light: #999999;
    --gray-dark: #2a2a2a;
    --partA-color: #FFD600;
    --partB-color: #FF4444;
    --partC-color: #00BFFF;
    --accent-green: #00E676;
    --feedback-bg: #0a0a0a;
    --feedback-border: #1a1a1a;
  }

- { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

body {
background: var(–bg-primary);
color: var(–white);
font-family: ‘Barlow’, sans-serif;
font-weight: 400;
line-height: 1.6;
min-height: 100vh;
overflow-x: hidden;
}

body::before {
content: ‘’;
position: fixed;
top: 0; left: 0;
width: 100%; height: 100%;
background-image: url(“data:image/svg+xml,%3Csvg viewBox=‘0 0 256 256’ xmlns=‘http://www.w3.org/2000/svg’%3E%3Cfilter id=‘noise’%3E%3CfeTurbulence type=‘fractalNoise’ baseFrequency=‘0.9’ numOctaves=‘4’ stitchTiles=‘stitch’/%3E%3C/filter%3E%3Crect width=‘100%25’ height=‘100%25’ filter=‘url(%23noise)’ opacity=‘0.03’/%3E%3C/svg%3E”);
pointer-events: none;
z-index: 9999;
}

.header {
position: relative;
padding: 60px 20px 40px;
text-align: center;
border-bottom: 1px solid var(–yellow-dim);
overflow: hidden;
background: linear-gradient(180deg, #0d0d00 0%, var(–bg-primary) 100%);
}

.header::before {
content: ‘’;
position: absolute;
top: -100px; left: 50%;
transform: translateX(-50%);
width: 500px; height: 500px;
background: radial-gradient(circle, var(–yellow-dim) 0%, transparent 70%);
pointer-events: none;
}

.header-tag {
font-family: ‘Barlow Condensed’, sans-serif;
font-weight: 400;
font-size: 13px;
letter-spacing: 6px;
text-transform: uppercase;
color: var(–gray);
margin-bottom: 10px;
}

.header-brand {
font-family: ‘Bebas Neue’, sans-serif;
font-size: clamp(56px, 12vw, 100px);
letter-spacing: 8px;
color: var(–yellow);
line-height: 1;
text-shadow: 0 0 60px var(–yellow-dim);
position: relative;
}

.header-sub {
font-family: ‘Barlow Condensed’, sans-serif;
font-weight: 600;
font-size: 15px;
letter-spacing: 10px;
text-transform: uppercase;
color: var(–gray-light);
margin-top: 8px;
}

.week-badge {
display: inline-block;
margin-top: 24px;
padding: 8px 28px;
border: 1px solid var(–yellow);
font-family: ‘Bebas Neue’, sans-serif;
font-size: 22px;
letter-spacing: 4px;
color: var(–yellow);
background: var(–yellow-soft);
}

.meso-info {
margin-top: 16px;
font-family: ‘Barlow’, sans-serif;
font-size: 13px;
color: var(–gray);
letter-spacing: 2px;
text-transform: uppercase;
}

.day-nav {
display: flex;
justify-content: center;
gap: 4px;
padding: 16px 16px;
flex-wrap: wrap;
position: sticky;
top: 0;
background: rgba(7,7,7,0.95);
backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
-webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
z-index: 100;
border-bottom: 1px solid #151515;
}

.day-nav a {
font-family: ‘Bebas Neue’, sans-serif;
font-size: 15px;
letter-spacing: 2px;
color: var(–gray);
text-decoration: none;
padding: 8px 14px;
border: 1px solid transparent;
transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.day-nav a:hover,
.day-nav a.active {
color: var(–yellow);
border-color: var(–yellow-dim);
background: var(–yellow-soft);
}

.container {
max-width: 900px;
margin: 0 auto;
padding: 20px 16px 80px;
}

.day-block {
margin-bottom: 48px;
animation: fadeUp 0.6s ease both;
}

@keyframes fadeUp {
from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(20px); }
to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
}

.day-header {
display: flex;
align-items: baseline;
gap: 16px;
margin-bottom: 24px;
padding-bottom: 14px;
border-bottom: 2px solid var(–yellow);
cursor: pointer;
user-select: none;
background: linear-gradient(180deg, #111100 0%, transparent 100%);
padding: 16px 16px 14px;
margin-left: -16px;
margin-right: -16px;
border-radius: 2px;
}

.day-number {
font-family: ‘Bebas Neue’, sans-serif;
font-size: 48px;
color: var(–yellow);
line-height: 1;
opacity: 0.25;
}

.day-name {
font-family: ‘Bebas Neue’, sans-serif;
font-size: 32px;
letter-spacing: 4px;
color: var(–yellow);
transition: text-shadow 0.3s;
}

.day-header:hover .day-name {
text-shadow: 0 0 20px var(–yellow-glow);
}

.day-toggle {
margin-left: auto;
font-size: 18px;
color: var(–yellow);
opacity: 0.5;
transition: transform 0.3s;
}

.day-block.collapsed .day-toggle { transform: rotate(-90deg); }
.day-block.collapsed .day-content { display: none; }

.day-content {
display: flex;
flex-direction: column;
gap: 16px;
}

.session {
background: var(–bg-card);
border-radius: 4px;
overflow: hidden;
border: 1px solid #181818;
transition: border-color 0.3s;
}

.session:hover { border-color: #252525; }

.session-header {
display: flex;
align-items: center;
gap: 12px;
padding: 14px 20px;
cursor: pointer;
user-select: none;
}

.session-indicator {
width: 3px;
height: 24px;
border-radius: 2px;
flex-shrink: 0;
}

.session.partA .session-indicator { background: var(–partA-color); }
.session.partB .session-indicator { background: var(–partB-color); }
.session.partC .session-indicator { background: var(–partC-color); }

.session-label {
font-family: ‘Barlow Condensed’, sans-serif;
font-weight: 700;
font-size: 13px;
letter-spacing: 3px;
text-transform: uppercase;
}

.session.partA .session-label { color: var(–partA-color); }
.session.partB .session-label { color: var(–partB-color); }
.session.partC .session-label { color: var(–partC-color); }

.session-toggle {
margin-left: auto;
font-size: 14px;
color: var(–gray);
transition: transform 0.3s;
}

.session.collapsed .session-toggle { transform: rotate(-90deg); }
.session.collapsed .session-body { display: none; }

.session-body { padding: 0 20px 20px; }

.block-title {
font-family: ‘Bebas Neue’, sans-serif;
font-size: 18px;
letter-spacing: 2px;
color: var(–yellow);
margin-bottom: 8px;
display: flex;
align-items: center;
gap: 8px;
}

.block-title::after {
content: ‘’;
flex: 1;
height: 1px;
background: var(–gray-dark);
}

.workout-detail {
font-family: ‘Barlow’, sans-serif;
font-size: 15px;
color: var(–white);
line-height: 1.75;
padding-left: 12px;
border-left: 1px solid var(–gray-dark);
margin-bottom: 8px;
}

.workout-detail strong {
color: var(–yellow);
font-weight: 600;
}

.workout-note {
font-size: 13px;
color: var(–gray);
font-style: italic;
margin-top: 4px;
padding-left: 12px;
}

.workout-sets {
font-family: ‘Barlow Condensed’, sans-serif;
font-weight: 600;
font-size: 14px;
color: var(–gray-light);
letter-spacing: 1px;
}

.wod-format {
display: inline-block;
font-family: ‘Bebas Neue’, sans-serif;
font-size: 16px;
letter-spacing: 2px;
padding: 4px 12px;
margin-bottom: 8px;
border: 1px solid;
}

.session.partA .wod-format { color: var(–partA-color); border-color: var(–partA-color); }
.session.partB .wod-format { color: var(–partB-color); border-color: var(–partB-color); }
.session.partC .wod-format { color: var(–partC-color); border-color: var(–partC-color); }

.sep {
height: 1px;
background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(–gray-dark), transparent);
margin: 12px 0;
}

.acc-tag {
font-family: ‘Barlow Condensed’, sans-serif;
font-size: 12px;
letter-spacing: 3px;
text-transform: uppercase;
color: var(–accent-green);
margin-bottom: 6px;
margin-top: 8px;
}

/* ═══ FEEDBACK ═══ */
.feedback-wrapper { margin-top: 8px; }

.feedback-toggle {
display: flex;
align-items: center;
gap: 10px;
padding: 12px 16px;
background: var(–feedback-bg);
border: 1px solid var(–feedback-border);
border-radius: 4px;
cursor: pointer;
user-select: none;
transition: all 0.3s;
}

.feedback-toggle:hover {
border-color: var(–yellow-dim);
background: #0c0c0c;
}

.feedback-icon { font-size: 16px; color: var(–yellow); opacity: 0.7; }

.feedback-toggle-label {
font-family: ‘Barlow Condensed’, sans-serif;
font-weight: 600;
font-size: 13px;
letter-spacing: 3px;
text-transform: uppercase;
color: var(–gray-light);
}

.feedback-arrow {
margin-left: auto;
font-size: 12px;
color: var(–gray);
transition: transform 0.3s;
}

.feedback-wrapper.collapsed .feedback-arrow { transform: rotate(-90deg); }
.feedback-wrapper.collapsed .feedback-body { display: none; }

.feedback-body {
padding: 16px 16px 20px;
background: var(–feedback-bg);
border: 1px solid var(–feedback-border);
border-top: none;
border-radius: 0 0 4px 4px;
}

.fb-section { margin-bottom: 14px; }
.fb-section:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

.fb-label {
font-family: ‘Barlow Condensed’, sans-serif;
font-weight: 700;
font-size: 12px;
letter-spacing: 2px;
text-transform: uppercase;
margin-bottom: 4px;
}

.fb-label.partA { color: var(–partA-color); }
.fb-label.partB { color: var(–partB-color); }
.fb-label.partC { color: var(–partC-color); }
.fb-label.general { color: var(–gray-light); }

.fb-text {
font-family: ‘Barlow’, sans-serif;
font-size: 14px;
line-height: 1.7;
color: #aaa;
padding-left: 10px;
border-left: 1px solid var(–gray-dark);
}

.fb-text strong { color: var(–white); font-weight: 600; }
.fb-text em { color: var(–yellow); font-style: normal; font-weight: 500; }

.fb-divider { height: 1px; background: var(–gray-dark); margin: 10px 0; }

.fb-contact {
margin-top: 10px;
font-family: ‘Barlow Condensed’, sans-serif;
font-size: 12px;
letter-spacing: 2px;
text-transform: uppercase;
color: var(–gray);
text-align: right;
}

.footer {
text-align: center;
padding: 40px 20px;
border-top: 1px solid #151515;
margin-top: 40px;
}

.footer-brand {
font-family: ‘Bebas Neue’, sans-serif;
font-size: 24px;
letter-spacing: 6px;
color: var(–yellow);
opacity: 0.3;
}

.footer-copy {
font-size: 12px;
color: var(–gray-dark);
margin-top: 8px;
letter-spacing: 2px;
}

@media (max-width: 600px) {
.header { padding: 40px 16px 30px; }
.day-number { font-size: 36px; }
.day-name { font-size: 24px; }
.session-body { padding: 0 14px 16px; }
.day-nav a { font-size: 13px; padding: 6px 10px; }
.day-header { margin-left: -8px; margin-right: -8px; padding: 12px 12px 12px; }
.feedback-body { padding: 12px; }
.fb-text { font-size: 13px; }
}

.day-block:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0s; }
.day-block:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.08s; }
.day-block:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.16s; }
.day-block:nth-child(4) { animation-delay: 0.24s; }
.day-block:nth-child(5) { animation-delay: 0.32s; }
.day-block:nth-child(6) { animation-delay: 0.4s; }
</style>

</head>
<body>

<header class="header">
  <div class="header-tag">Functional Development Program</div>
  <div class="header-brand">HUMANFITS</div>
  <div class="header-sub">Stronger · Faster · Unbreakable</div>
  <div class="week-badge">WEEK 1</div>
  <div class="meso-info">Mesocycle 1 of 6 — Foundation Phase</div>
</header>

<nav class="day-nav">
  <a href="#day1">MON</a>
  <a href="#day2">TUE</a>
  <a href="#day3">WED</a>
  <a href="#day4">THU</a>
  <a href="#day5">FRI</a>
  <a href="#day6">SAT</a>
</nav>

<main class="container">

<!-- ═══════════ MONDAY ═══════════ -->

<section class="day-block" id="day1">
  <div class="day-header" onclick="toggleDay(this)">
    <span class="day-number">01</span>
    <span class="day-name">MONDAY</span>
    <span class="day-toggle">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="day-content">

```
<div class="session partA">
  <div class="session-header" onclick="toggleSession(this)">
    <div class="session-indicator"></div>
    <span class="session-label">Part A — Fuerza</span>
    <span class="session-toggle">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="session-body">
    <div class="block-title">Snatch Pull + Hang Snatch (below knee)</div>
    <div class="workout-detail">
      Every 60s x 10 sets (5 rounds of 2+1)<br>
      <span class="workout-sets">@ 60-65%</span>
    </div>
    <div class="workout-note">Focus: Slow pull, fast turnover</div>
    <div class="sep"></div>
    <div class="block-title">Front Squat</div>
    <div class="workout-detail">
      Every 75s x 5 sets of 4<br>
      <span class="workout-sets">@ 68-70% — Tempo 31X1</span>
    </div>
    <div class="workout-note">Elbows high throughout</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="session partB">
  <div class="session-header" onclick="toggleSession(this)">
    <div class="session-indicator"></div>
    <span class="session-label">Part B — Metcon</span>
    <span class="session-toggle">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="session-body">
    <div class="wod-format">AMRAP 16:00</div>
    <div class="workout-detail">
      3 Muscle-Ups<br>
      6 Squat Snatch 50/35 kg<br>
      9 Box Jump Over 24/20"<br>
      12 T2B<br>
      <em style="color:var(--gray);">Rest 1:00 between rounds</em>
    </div>
    <div class="sep"></div>
    <div class="acc-tag">Accessories</div>
    <div class="workout-detail">
      <strong>Shoulder Stability + Overhead Integrity</strong> — 3 Sets<br>
      10 Cuban Press (light)<br>
      15 Banded Pull-Aparts<br>
      1:00 Overhead KB Hold/arm
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="session partC">
  <div class="session-header" onclick="toggleSession(this)">
    <div class="session-indicator"></div>
    <span class="session-label">Part C — 2nd Session</span>
    <span class="session-toggle">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="session-body">
    <div class="wod-format">5 Rounds For Time (28:00 Cap)</div>
    <div class="workout-detail">
      400m Run<br>
      15 KB Swings 24/16 kg<br>
      12 Push-Ups<br>
      9 Goblet Squats 24/16 kg<br>
      6 Burpees
    </div>
    <div class="workout-note">Pace: Conversational first 3 rounds, push last 2</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="feedback-wrapper collapsed">
  <div class="feedback-toggle" onclick="toggleFeedback(this)">
    <span class="feedback-icon">◆</span>
    <span class="feedback-toggle-label">Notas del día</span>
    <span class="feedback-arrow">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="feedback-body">
    <div class="fb-section">
      <div class="fb-label partA">Part A — Fuerza</div>
      <div class="fb-text">
        Hoy arrancas el mesociclo con <em>Snatch Pull + Hang Snatch desde debajo de la rodilla</em>. Tu objetivo es construir un tirón limpio desde cero. Tira lento, siente la barra pegada al muslo, y solo mete velocidad en el turnover. <strong>Si notas que abres los brazos antes de terminar la extensión de cadera, baja al 55% sin pensarlo</strong> — la técnica manda esta semana. En el Front Squat con tempo 31X1, la pausa de 1 segundo abajo te va a exponer si tu core no está activado o si los codos caen. Si los codos bajan, el peso es demasiado. Mantén el pecho alto y los codos apuntando a la pared de enfrente.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="fb-divider"></div>
    <div class="fb-section">
      <div class="fb-label partB">Part B — Metcon</div>
      <div class="fb-text">
        El minuto de descanso entre rondas no es para que te enfríes — es para que cada ronda sea de calidad. <strong>Si no tienes Muscle-Ups, haz 5 Chest-to-Bar + 3 Strict Dips</strong> — mantiene el estímulo de pulling + pressing. El Squat Snatch a 50/35 debe permitirte hacer touch-and-go en sets de 2-3 mínimo. Si estás haciendo singles desde la primera rep, baja el peso. Los accesorios de hombro después del WOD son <em>obligatorios</em>: acabas de meter volumen overhead y tu estabilidad escapular necesita atención directa. No te los saltes.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="fb-divider"></div>
    <div class="fb-section">
      <div class="fb-label partC">Part C — 2nd Session</div>
      <div class="fb-text">
        Las primeras 3 rondas deben ser conversacionales de verdad — si no puedes hablar, vas demasiado fuerte. <em>Las últimas 2 rondas son donde empujas el threshold.</em> El 400m Run marca la dinámica de cada ronda: <strong>si tu run supera los 2:10, el resto de la ronda se contamina.</strong> Los KB Swings son American (extensión completa overhead). Los Goblet Squats con pausa de 1 segundo abajo para que mantengas la calidad incluso con fatiga acumulada.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="fb-contact">¿Dudas? Escríbeme al privado</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

  </div>
</section>

<!-- ═══════════ TUESDAY ═══════════ -->

<section class="day-block" id="day2">
  <div class="day-header" onclick="toggleDay(this)">
    <span class="day-number">02</span>
    <span class="day-name">TUESDAY</span>
    <span class="day-toggle">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="day-content">

```
<div class="session partA">
  <div class="session-header" onclick="toggleSession(this)">
    <div class="session-indicator"></div>
    <span class="session-label">Part A — Fuerza</span>
    <span class="session-toggle">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="session-body">
    <div class="block-title">Romanian Deadlift</div>
    <div class="workout-detail">
      Every 75s x 4 sets of 8<br>
      <span class="workout-sets">@ 65%</span>
    </div>
    <div class="workout-note">Slow eccentric, hamstring loading</div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="session partB">
  <div class="session-header" onclick="toggleSession(this)">
    <div class="session-indicator"></div>
    <span class="session-label">Part B — Metcon</span>
    <span class="session-toggle">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="session-body">
    <div class="wod-format">For Time</div>
    <div class="workout-detail">
      500m Row<br>
      50 Pistols (alternating)<br>
      1000m BikeErg<br>
      50 GHD Sit-Ups<br>
      500m Row<br>
      30 Pistols (alternating)<br>
      1000m BikeErg<br>
      30 GHD Sit-Ups
    </div>
    <div class="sep"></div>
    <div class="acc-tag">Accessories</div>
    <div class="workout-detail">
      3 Sets<br>
      10 GHD Hip Extensions (slow)<br>
      30s Side Plank/side<br>
      15 Banded Good Mornings
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="session partC">
  <div class="session-header" onclick="toggleSession(this)">
    <div class="session-indicator"></div>
    <span class="session-label">Part C — 2nd Session</span>
    <span class="session-toggle">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="session-body">
    <div class="wod-format">EMOM 24:00 (6-min cycle)</div>
    <div class="workout-detail">
      Min 1: 100m Run<br>
      Min 2: 12 Wall Balls 9/6 kg<br>
      Min 3: 12 Push-Ups<br>
      Min 4: 12 Cal Bike<br>
      Min 5: 12 Box Jumps 24/20"<br>
      Min 6: 36 DB Russian Twists
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="feedback-wrapper collapsed">
  <div class="feedback-toggle" onclick="toggleFeedback(this)">
    <span class="feedback-icon">◆</span>
    <span class="feedback-toggle-label">Notas del día</span>
    <span class="feedback-arrow">▼</span>
  </div>
  <div class="feedback-body">
    <div class="fb-section">
      <div class="fb-label partA">Part A — Fuerza</div>
      <div class="fb-text">
        Hoy es día de RDL — la clave está en la <em>excéntrica controlada</em>. Quiero que tardes 3 segundos en bajar la barra desde la cadera hasta debajo de la rodilla. Si pierdes la tensión en los isquios o tu espalda se redondea, el peso es demasiado alto. <strong>El RDL no es un deadlift con piernas rectas</strong> — mantén un slight bend constante en las rodillas y bisagra 100% desde la cadera. 8 reps al 65% debería generarte un pump serio en isquios sin comprometer la posición lumbar.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="fb-divider"></div>
    <div class="fb-section">
      <div class="fb-label partB">Part B — Metcon</div>
      <div class="fb-text">
        50 Pistols + 50 GHD Sit-Ups en la primera mitad van a acumular fatiga seria en cuádriceps y hip flexors. <strong>Si no tienes el Pistol completo, hazlo a una caja o con banda</strong> — no lo cambies por air squats, porque pierdes toda la intención unilateral. Los GHD Sit-Ups deben ser ROM completo pero controlados: si empiezas a hacer swing agresivo para ganar velocidad, corta las reps. El Row entre bloques es tu <em>active recovery</em> — pace de 2:00-2:10/500m, no más rápido. Los accesorios refuerzan exactamente la cadena posterior que el WOD acaba de castigar.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="fb-divider"></div>
    <div class="fb-section">
      <div class="fb-label partC">Part C — 2nd Session</div>
      <div class="fb-text">
        EMOM de 24 minutos con ciclo de 6 estaciones — harás 4 rotaciones completas. Cada minuto debes completar el trabajo en 40-45 segundos para tener 15-20s de transición y recovery. <strong>Si alguna estación te come el minuto entero, escala las reps.</strong> Los 36 DB Russian Twists en el minuto 6 son el momento más comprometido — llegan con fatiga acumulada de todo lo anterior. Pies elevados, rotación completa de torso. No muevas solo los brazos.
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="fb-contact">¿Dudas? Escríbeme al privado</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

